## Examples

```bash
# 1. Discover what's available
hexlane integration list
hexlane integration show my-app

# 2. Count rows in a table (TOON by default)
hexlane sql query my-app-db-prod \
  --sql "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM my_table"

# 3. Look up a specific record — preview SQL before running
hexlane sql query my-app-db-prod \
  --sql "SELECT * FROM my_table WHERE id = :id" \
  --param id=123 --dry-run
hexlane sql query my-app-db-prod \
  --sql "SELECT * FROM my_table WHERE id = :id" \
  --param id=123

# 4. Use PostgreSQL ::type cast syntax safely alongside :params
hexlane sql query my-app-db-prod \
  --sql "SELECT id::text, created_at::date FROM orders WHERE status = :status" \
  --param status=active

# 5. HTTP call — structured envelope { status, body } in TOON by default
hexlane http call my-app-api-prod /api/v1/resource

# 6. HTTP POST with body
hexlane http call my-app-api-prod /api/v1/resource \
  -m POST --body '{"key": "value"}'

# 7. Debug a failing command
hexlane http call my-app-api-prod /api/v1/resource --debug

# 8. Force fresh credential after 401
hexlane credential revoke --target my-app-api-prod
```

---

## Output Format Guide

**TOON is the default output format for all commands.** Use `--json` only when you need JSON specifically.

| Situation                             | Use                                          |
| ------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| Normal usage (rows, API responses)    | (no flag — TOON is the default)              |
| Need JSON format explicitly           | `--json`                                     |
| Checking HTTP status / response shape | (no flag needed — envelope always in output) |
| Credential / connection issues        | `--debug`                                    |
| Preview SQL without hitting the DB    | `--dry-run`                                  |
| Preview op execution without running  | `--dry-run`                                  |
